Lab 6: KQL in Advanced Hunting
📚 Section Overview
Learn how to use Kusto Query Language (KQL) for advanced hunting in Microsoft Defender to proactively investigate and detect threats.

🎯 Learning Objectives
Understand KQL syntax and structure.
Use KQL to filter, sort, and aggregate data.
Write and execute KQL queries in Defender Advanced Hunting.
Apply KQL to real-world threat hunting scenarios.
🛠️ Prerequisites
Basic understanding of cybersecurity concepts and familiarity with Kusto query language.

🗂️ Session Outline
1. Introduction to KQL (10 mins)

Overview of KQL and its use in Defender Advanced Hunting.
Basic syntax and structure.
2. Basic Querying (20 mins)

Writing simple queries to retrieve data.
Filtering with where.
Sorting with order by.
3. Aggregations (20 mins)

Using summarize for aggregations.
Common functions: count, sum, avg.
Grouping with by.
4. Advanced Techniques (20 mins)

Joining tables with join.
Creating columns with extend.
Selecting columns with project.
